Marlin Financial Group , a U.K.-based
buyer of non-performing consumer debt, signed an 80 million-
pound ($128 million) credit line arranged by Royal Bank of
Scotland Group Plc and  Investec Plc. (INVP)   The three-year loan will boost the companyâ€™s capacity for
further debt purchases, according to a  statement  on the website
of Duke Street Capital Ltd, owner of a majority stake in the
Worthing, England-based business.  Marlin has invested almost 100 million pounds in U.K. non-
performing loans in the last year, about 10 percent of the
